<TITLE> NBR chairman, four other secretaries shuffled </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Oct 18 (bdnews24.com)  Badiur Rahman who was appointed as the country's chief revenue collector on Jan 21 was transferred in a major administrative reshuffle Thursday. According to an establishment ministry circular, Badiur Rahman, secretary of the Internal Resources Division and chairman of the National Board of Revenue, has been transferred to the food and disaster management ministry. Muhammad Abdul Majid, member of the Planning Commission, became NBR chairman. Abdul Majid was promoted secretary on Sept 18. Badiur Rahman's transfer was a much-talked-about issue for the administration and the media Wednesday. Three other secretaries have also been transferred, the circular said. Food and disaster management secretary Dhiraj Malakar has been transferred to the Planning Commission as member. AMM Nasir Uddin of the Energy and Mineral Resources Division became member of the Planning Commission. Mohammad Mohsin, executive chairman of the Board of Investment, has been transferred to the Energy and Mineral Resources Division. bdnews24.c
